disks, and Amiga magazines were also sent full review copies of Putty Squad, for which it received critical success. \n \nPutty Squad is a platform game in which the player controls an amorphous blue blob, tasked with rescuing imprisoned putties. The player's putty can stretch in a variety of ways: sidewards to cover ground faster, squash flat to absorb pick-up items, stretch upwards to climb, morph a fist to attack, or inflate to float upwards. \n \nPutty can collect stars that increase his attack power: at first increasing the potency of his punch, but later allowing him to blow darts, electrocute enemies or throw bombs. This star power is reduced every time Putty is hit by an enemy.","collection":3408,"popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[26848,27239,1070,4432,1073,41118,38305,10039,1188,1404],"tags":[27,268435464,1073741828],"developers":[1234],"publishers":[1271],"category":0,"player_perspectives":[4],"game_modes":[1],"themes":[27],"genres":[8],"first_release_date":788832000000,"platforms":[16,19],"release_dates":[{"category":2,"platform":19,"date":788832000000,"region":1,"human":"1994","y":1994,"m":12},{"category":0,"platform":16,"date":1387843200000,"human":"2013-Dec-24","y":2013,"m":12}],"screenshots":[{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/n5tnwgicvlkzmedhzomu.jpg","cloudinary_id":"n5tnwgicvlkzmedhzomu","width":960,"height":540},{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/cai2ageivfdjvzzrqwxw.jpg","cloudinary_id":"cai2ageivfdjvzzrqwxw","width":960,"height":540},{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/xcwgla8lyyfvs7oewgok.jpg","cloudinary_id":"xcwgla8lyyfvs7oewgok","width":960,"height":540},{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/mccvcwfeurajawk2jpok.jpg","cloudinary_id":"mccvcwfeurajawk2jpok","width":960,"height":540},{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/wuocay4emtizryd5s5g3.jpg","cloudinary_id":"wuocay4emtizryd5s5g3","width":960,"height":540},{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/sd43pdgiopgutg6xnsk6.jpg","cloudinary_id":"sd43pdgiopgutg6xnsk6","width":960,"height":540},{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/plwsleduch41u0gelkky.jpg","cloudinary_id":"plwsleduch41u0gelkky","width":960,"height":540}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/k81qf6st1vrolzk6v3oo.jpg","cloudinary_id":"k81qf6st1vrolzk6v3oo","width":640,"height":442},"websites":[{"category":3,"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Putty_Squad"}]},{"id":39022,"name":"Putty","slug":"putty","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/putty","created_at":1498118481527,"updated_at":1513070602571,"summary":"Putty is a game developed by System 3 and released in 1992 for the Amiga. \n \nIn Putty, the player controls a blue blob with eyes. Putty has many moves that he could use to attack enemies or to navigate around the level. These abilities include being able to stretch out upwards, downwards, left and right to access far-off ledges. He also has the ability to inflate. This allows him to provide a cushioned landing for any falling bots. Over-inflation also acts as a \"smart bomb\", with Putty bursting, killing all of the enemies on the screen, whilst reducing his health in the process. \n \nThe levels in Putty are laid out vertically, with the screen scrolling up and down. The levels contain regular platforms, as well as \"solid\" ledges that Putty can not move through, and other special tiles including electric platforms and bounce pads.","collection":3408,"popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[55752,36868,26848,44177,10039,76098,68324,51464,27239,1070],"tags":[1,27,268435464,536871208,536871262,536872285,536872961,536875879,536876585],"category":0,"keywords":[296,350,1373,2049,4967,5673],"themes":[1,27],"genres":[8],"first_release_date":696902400000,"platforms":[16],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":16,"date":696902400000,"region":8,"human":"1992-Feb-01","y":1992,"m":2}],"alternative_names":[{"name":"Putty Moon","comment":"Other"},{"name":"Super Putty","comment":"Other"}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/gl3hl3tnfnaog9ifq2nl.jpg","cloudinary_id":"gl3hl3tnfnaog9ifq2nl","width":300,"height":349}},{"id":39023,"name":"Dyna Blaster","slug":"dyna-blaster","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/dyna-blaster","created_at":1498118483797,"updated_at":1520719728456,"summary":"Dyna Blaster or Dynablaster is a name that has been given to the European releases of the game of the Bomberman. It's a strategic, maze-based video game franchise originally developed by Hudson Soft. \n \nMost games in the Bomberman franchise largely revolve around two modes of play; single player campaigns where the player must defeat enemies and reach an exit to progress through levels, and multiplayer modes where players must attempt to eliminate each other and be the last one standing. Gameplay involves strategically placing down bombs, which explode in multiple directions after a certain amount of time, in order to destroy obstacles and kill enemies and other players. The player can pick up various power-ups, giving them benefits such as larger explosions or the ability to place more bombs down at a time. The player is killed if they touch an enemy or get caught up in a bomb's explosion, including their own, requiring players to be cautious of their own bomb placement.","collection":549,"popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[106530,89074,94873,19222,27880,101563,104675,106275,90108,80174],"tags":[268435464,268435465,1073741827],"developers":[864],"publishers":[7041],"category":0,"player_perspectives":[3],"game_modes":[1,2],"genres":[8,9],"first_release_date":696902400000,"pulse_count":1,"platforms":[16],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":16,"date":696902400000,"region":8,"human":"1992-Feb-01","y":1992,"m":2}],"screenshots":[{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/rac1ec4zpqqppzd1fskp.jpg","cloudinary_id":"rac1ec4zpqqppzd1fskp","width":800,"height":600}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb