right (across the bottom of the screen), with a single button to make it fire shots up at the various types of enemies - and the first stage will see it fighting a formation of \"Super Mosquitoes\", which are worth 20 points apiece. The second stage, which sees a dotted orange line under the ship, will see it fighting a formation of \"Hovering Attackers\" which are worth 30 points apiece, and the third stage will see it fighting a formation of \"Demon Flies\", which are worth 40; some of the \"Demon Flies\" will leave \"Spy Aliens\" when killed, which will fall down to the bottom of the screen underneath that line, and try to stab the ship from behind. The only way to kill them (for 100 points apiece), is to destroy the \"Killer King\" when he appears - and the fourth and last unique stage will see the ship fighting a formation of \"Rolling Fires\", which are worth 50 points apiece and will also occasionally leave \"Spy Aliens\" behind when killed. After the last unique stage has been cleared, the four-stage cycle will start all over again.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[68287,36950,10209,28029,64204,27314,10213,71455,26766,25300],"tags":[18,268435461,536871078,536871859,536871882,536872352,536875064,536876798],"category":0,"keywords":[166,947,970,1440,4152,5886],"themes":[18],"genres":[5],"first_release_date":318211200000,"platforms":[52],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":52,"date":318211200000,"region":8,"human":"1980-Feb-01","y":1980,"m":2}],"alternative_names":[{"name":"Gingateikoku no Gyakushuu","comment":"Other"}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/x6wdbb3pdhykz5ks2jif.jpg","cloudinary_id":"x6wdbb3pdhykz5ks2jif","width":850,"height":1197}},{"id":40013,"name":"Baluba-louk no Densetsu","slug":"baluba-louk-no-densetsu","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/baluba-louk-no-densetsu","created_at":1498466774778,"updated_at":1500233955428,"summary":"Baluba-Louk No Densetsu is a platform arcade game released by Able in 1986. An explorer must get all the treasure chests while avoiding the monsters.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[1070,41118,38305,1073,1188,89495,51942,51247,51203,50992],"tags":[268435464],"category":0,"genres":[8],"first_release_date":507600000000,"platforms":[52],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":52,"date":507600000000,"region":8,"human":"1986-Feb-01","y":1986,"m":2}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/m3tzbglomgigtwvkunna.jpg","cloudinary_id":"m3tzbglomgigtwvkunna","width":850,"height":1209}},{"id":40014,"name":"Atari Soccer","slug":"atari-soccer","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/atari-soccer","created_at":1498466778496,"updated_at":1500233937117,"summary":"Atari Soccer is, as the naming implies, a soccer arcade game that was released by Atari in 1980; it utilizes a Motorola M6502 (running at 750 KHz), and the players must use a trackball to take control of a player (two on each team, and if there are only two players, the CPU shall fill in for 3P and 4P), with two buttons for kicking the ball with their left and right feet. The human-controlled players will be indicated by the \"squares\" (1P and 3P) and \"crosses\" (2P and 4P) upon their heads - and just like in real association football, whoever has the most goals when the timer has run out wins the game. 1P and 2P's team is black, and 3P and 4P's team is white; and as with the four-player version of Atari's earlier American football game, one credit buys a two-player game and two buy a four-player game.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[46820,39665,101684,101567,101100,100907,100887,100879,100863,100832],"tags":[268435470],"category":0,"genres":[14],"first_release_date":286675200000,"platforms":[52],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":52,"date":286675200000,"region":8,"human":"1979-Feb-01","y":1979,"m":2}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/qvocnpj4orbiiapdbsjd.jpg","cloudinary_id":"qvocnpj4orbiiapdbsjd","width":850,"height":1102}},{"id":40015,"name":"Armored Car","slug":"armored-car","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/armored-car","created_at":1498466779586,"updated_at":1500237681209,"summary":"You drive a money van (the armoured car) through as it scrolls from right to left. Some intersections are marked with directions. You pick up money to deliver to banks while avoiding criminals by dropping saw horses on the road. Fuel levels must be replenished at gas stations along the way.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"category":0,"genres":[15],"first_release_date":349833600000,"platforms":[52],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":52,"date":349833600000,"region":8,"human":"1981-Feb-01","y":1981,"m":2}]},{"id":40016,"name":"Ark Area","slug":"ark-area","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/ark-area","created_at":1498466781923,"updated_at":1500237681558,"summary":"Ark Area is a scrolling futuristic shoot 'em up arcade game released by UPL in 1987 in Japan only. You control a spacecraft and shoot enemies, collect power-ups, and defeat bosses to advance up to 23 levels. It is the sequel to the video arcade game Nova 2001.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"category":0,"genres":[5],"first_release_date":539136000000,"platforms":[52],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":52,"date":539136000000,"region":8,"human":"1987-Feb-01","y":1987,"m":2}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/utx0gkicvdsllmr6pov0.jpg","cloudinary_id":"utx0gkicvdsllmr6pov0","width":1440,"height":1080}},{"id":40017,"name":"Sengoku Ace","slug":"sengoku-ace","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/sengoku-ace","created_at":1498466784869,"updated_at":1531324430114,"summary":"Sengoku Ace (Sengoku Ace (戦国エース Sengoku Ēsu)), fully titled Sengoku Ace: Tengai Episode I and also known as Samurai Aces in the English version, is a vertically-scrolling shoot 'em up video game originally released in the arcades by Psikyo in 1993. The first game by Psikyo, Sengoku Ace was designed by Shin Nakamura, the creator of Aero Fighters (Sonic Wings) and the company's founder. \n \nThe game features 21 endings, different for various characters and 2-player pairings.","storyline":"The science fantasy story of Sengoku Ace resolves around the six Feudal Japan (Sengoku period) characters sent on a mission to stop an evil cult and rescue the shogun's kidnapped daughter, princess Tsukihime (Moon Princess), before she can be used as a sacrifice to resurrect their demon god.","collection":4814,"popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[103281,103298,103301,103020,46265,41258,28029,19341,42992,32902],"tags":[268435461,1073741828],"developers":[15898,2888],"publishers":[15899,1215],"category":0,"player_perspectives":[4],"game_modes":[1],"keywords":[166,844,1679],"themes":[18],"genres":[5],"first_release_date":735436800000,"platforms":[52,55],"release_dates":[{"category":7,"platform":55,"human":"TBD"},{"category":0,"platform":52,"date":735436800000,"human":"1993-Apr-22","y":1993,"m":4},{"category":0,"platform":52,"date":735436800000,"region":8,"human":"1993-Apr-22","y":1993,"m":4}],"alternative_names":[{"name":"戦国エース Sengoku Ēsu","comment":"Japanese title"},{"name":"Sengoku Ace: Tengai Episode I ","comment":"Japanese title"},{"name":"Samurai Aces","comment":"English"}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/w5dh8hbbmo1fk6pakwpc.jpg","cloudinary_id":"w5dh8hbbmo1fk6pakwpc","width":335,"height":477}},{"id":40018,"name":"Senjyo","slug":"senjyo","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/senjyo","created_at":1498466789332,"updated_at":1513068156721,"summary":"The title of this game translates from Japanese as 'Battlefield'. The simple gameplay involves the player controlling a fixed turret on a tank shooting oncoming alien enemies through a cross-hair target. A certain number of enemies must be destroyed to progress to the next stage. The original arcade cabinet was a cocktail table.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[36608,34919,16468,23175,40524,68324,1070,28029,59516,55289],"tags":[1,536870915,536875303],"category":0,"keywords":[3,4391],"themes":[1],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/vv11tpifpqapygii76pg.jpg","cloudinary_id":"vv11tpifpqapygii76pg","width":224,"height":256}},{"id":40019,"name":"Sinbad Mystery","slug":"sinbad-mystery","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/sinbad-mystery","created_at":1498466791082,"updated_at":1500233892461,"popularity":1.333333333333333,"category":0,"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/nte717g5tghxn6berxwf.jpg","cloudinary_id":"nte717g5tghxn6berxwf","width":850,"height":1098}},{"id":40020,"name":"Galivan - Cosmo Police","slug":"galivan-cosmo-police","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/galivan-cosmo-police","created_at":1498466922688,"updated_at":1500238083640,"summary":"'Cosmo Police Galivan' is an action game that was released from Nichibutsu in 1985. Players are transformed into 'Galivan' with putting in hand the power crystal, to destroy the universe criminal organization 'Aku'.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"category":0,"genres":[4],"first_release_date":476064000000,"platforms":[52],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":52,"date":476064000000,"region":8,"human":"1985-Feb-01","y":1985,"m":2}]},{"id":40021,"name":"Cosmic Alien","slug":"cosmic-alien","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/cosmic-alien","created_at":1498466924168,"updated_at":1500234158341,"summary":"Cosmic Alien is an arcade game that is a clone of Galaxian. Players control a gun at the bottom of the screen that shoots at aliens (which are known as \"chiefs\", \"guards\", \"commanders\", or \"soldiers\") that are in a formation overhead. Aliens begin peeling off the formation and fly towards the bottom of the screen while dropping bombs. There are two flagship-type aliens (chiefs) at the top of the screen that can fly accompanied with one or more escort (guard) aliens; shooting one or more of the guards before shooting a chief will increase the amount of the chief’s score. If a player does not shoot an alien (or if it doesn’t ram the player’s gun) during its attack run it will return to the formation. \n \nThere are a few differences with Galaxian, as sometimes aliens will return to the formation without dropping below the bottom of the screen (and then reappearing at the top). They also can shoot off a wide horizontal string of bombs, rather than individual shots like on Galaxian. If the last alien on a level (known as \"screens\") is left alone long enough, it will turn into a big winged creature. Also, aliens start changing form: by the third screen, they start resembling winged demons once they leave the formation, plus the player’s gun is bumped up a notch, giving them less time to react to the aliens’ attacks. \n \nPlayers start off with three guns, which can be lost by being hit by an alien or bomb and the game will end if there are no more guns in reserve. An extra gun is awarded at 5,000 points.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[46892,41258,76246,19341,28029,32902,97018,96550,93794,88910],"tags":[268435461],"category":0,"genres":[5],"first_release_date":318211200000,"platforms":[52],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":52,"date":318211200000,"region":8,"human":"1980-Feb-01","y":1980,"m":2}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/q06h8ac4fjnkwqjk1mvx.jpg","cloudinary_id":"q06h8ac4fjnkwqjk1mvx","width":850,"height":1108}},{"id":40022,"name":"Cop 01","slug":"cop-01","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/cop-01","created_at":1498466926252,"updated_at":1500234149802,"popularity":1.333333333333333,"category":0,"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/ghhutuqyivuuyotn1osg.jpg","cloudinary_id":"ghhutuqyivuuyotn1osg","width":850,"height":1192}},{"id":40023,"name":"Chicken Shift","slug":"chicken-shift","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/chicken-shift","created_at":1498466928561,"updated_at":1500234131204,"summary":"The gameplay in Chicken Shift is relatively simple. There will be a string of eggs you have to guide to safety by shifting the posit