height":440}},{"id":40754,"name":"Solar Plexus","slug":"solar-plexus","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/solar-plexus","created_at":1498483971292,"updated_at":1513001159048,"summary":"What starts out as a routine hunt for salvage in the far reaches of the galaxy turns into a white-knuckle fight for survival in Solar Plexus, the first Atari 2600 release by independent game developer JessCREATIONS*, Co. It'll take sharp reflexes to keep your starskimmer full of fuel and away from the wildly unpredictable artificial sun which threatens to make every move your last! \nThe Solar Plexus increases in speed and mutates into new, more dangerous forms as you continue to play. If one fiery orb bouncing around the screen was hard enough for you to handle, just wait until you have to deal with two, or even three of them! Only the best players will last long enough to witness the final form of this relentless foe.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[34919,19341,25311,44242,36608,28465,37419,54999,55715,33603],"tags":[1,268435469],"category":0,"themes":[1],"genres":[13],"first_release_date":1114905600000,"platforms":[59],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":59,"date":1114905600000,"region":8,"human":"2005-May-01","y":2005,"m":5}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/ccghhfaytyo1pwbw2qxf.jpg","cloudinary_id":"ccghhfaytyo1pwbw2qxf","width":400,"height":484}},{"id":40755,"name":"Rubik's Cube 3-D","slug":"rubiks-cube-3-d","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/rubiks-cube-3-d","created_at":1498483974032,"updated_at":1500246952307,"summary":"Can you solve it? \n \nAre you up to the challenge of trying to master the Cube? Restore all of its six sides to the original colors in this mesmerizing 3D translation of the hit puzzle game synonymous with the 80's! \n \nWhen solved, every face of Rubik's Cube is a solid color. Once you start turning, twisting and flipping, it's easy to mix up the colors. Not to worry - Rubik's Cube can be set right any mixed-up combination.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[19222,41348,10225,27266,14246,60044,236,27725,101980,101976],"tags":[268435465],"category":0,"genres":[9],"first_release_date":389059200000,"platforms":[59],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":59,"date":389059200000,"region":8,"human":"1982-May-01","y":1982,"m":5}]},{"id":40756,"name":"Pressure Gauge","slug":"pressure-gauge","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/pressure-gauge","created_at":1498483977960,"updated_at":1512855487910,"summary":"Pressure Gauge is a game that was written back in 2000 as a college exercise by John K. Harvey. It's not much to look at graphically, but this game is a \"twitch\" game that just may have you reaching for the reset button for \"just one more round\". The game was inspired by a mini-game in the Playstation title \"Brave Fencer Musashi\". \nGameplay is simple. The initial screen says \"Pressure Gauge\"; from here, you can hit select to see the first homebrew attempt at a scrolling text demo (which would later be reformulated and released as StickyNotes), or you can hit the reset button to start the game. A little song will play, and you're on your way! The interface is as simple as can be-- it only uses the button. Push the button precisely when the leftmost \"filling gauge\" is lined up with the \"range\" on the left of it. Get within range, and you'll be rewarded-- slightly. The second gauge will fill up, just a little bit. You need to have a certain amount of successes in order to fill the second gauge all the way to the top, to advance to the next level. A miss results in the second gauge decreasing slightly, so you need quick skills to fill up the second gauge completely in order to advance to the next level. The rightmost bar counts down on time; run out, and it's game over!","popularity":1.0,"games":[19222,41348,10225,27266,14246,60044,236,27725,101980,101976],"tags":[268435465],"category":0,"genres":[9],"first_release_date":957139200000,"platforms":[59],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":59,"date":957139200000,"region":8,"human":"2000-May-01","y":2000,"m":5}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/sawee2iskbeat9dihpbc.jpg","cloudinary_id":"sawee2iskbeat9dihpbc","width":640,"height":420}},{"id":40757,"name":"Brick Kick","slug":"brick-kick","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/brick-kick","created_at":1498483988483,"updated_at":1500246927081,"summary":"Brick Kick is an Action game, published by R. J. P. G., which was cancelled before it was released","popularity":1.0,"games":[36608,2940,40524,34919,71581,29660,1070,23175,76438,16468],"tags":[1],"category":0,"themes":[1]},{"id":40758,"name":"Pizza Chef","slug":"pizza-chef","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/pizza-chef","created_at":1498483990523,"updated_at":1500246918569,"summary":"Try this fun pizza making game. You have a limited time to make an eight-ingredient pizza. For this, you should get the right ingredients and in the same order as they are listed – and also the aproppriate utensils. When you finally put everything at the eight preparation tables, take the pizza to a hot oven to bake. If you manage to do it all, congratulations! Try all the 25 recipe variations and show your skills and technique in pizza making.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[44242,24491,28465,75579,75275,34919,75102,33603,36962,55888],"tags":[268435469],"category":0,"genres":[13],"first_release_date":420595200000,"platforms":[59],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":59,"date":420595200000,"region":8,"human":"1983-May-01","y":1983,"m":5}]},{"id":40759,"name":"Mondo Pong","slug":"mondo-pong","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/mondo-pong","created_at":1498483992217,"updated_at":1500246910000,"summary":"Mondo Pong was Piero Cavina's first programming effort on the Atari 2600 and is an evil variation on the game that started it all, Pong. In this version there are two balls and they each have a mind of their own! Sometimes the ball will double back at you after you hit it, other times it might just spin around in circles for a bit, keeping you on your toes as you wait for it to shoot off in some direction (hopefully not at you!) \n \nThere are several game variations that allow you to select one or two players and a score limit of 15 or 45. There is also a normal vs. hard option, but that is not implemented in this version of Mondo Pong. \n \nThis is an Alpha Version of Mondo Pong as it was never completed! Therefore, the game doesn't have the polish you might expect from a finished game and there may be a few bugs. Nevertheless, it's still an interesting concept and a hoot to play.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[46820,39665,101684,101567,101100,100907,100887,100879,100863,100832],"tags":[268435470],"category":0,"genres":[14],"first_release_date":1493683200000,"pulse_count":1,"platforms":[59],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":59,"date":1493683200000,"region":8,"human":"2017-May-02","y":2017,"m":5}]},{"id":40760,"name":"Mine Sweeper","slug":"mine-sweeper","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/mine-sweeper","created_at":1498483995923,"updated_at":1500246901136,"summary":"Have you ever wanted to play the Windows time waster on your old Atari 2600? Well now you can!","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[19222,41348,10225,27266,14246,60044,236,27725,101980,101976],"tags":[268435465],"category":0,"genres":[9]},{"id":40761,"name":"Mind Maze","slug":"mind-maze","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/mind-maze","created_at":1498483997169,"updated_at":1523345014656,"summary":"MIND MAZE - is a logical competitive game based on capturing of the playing field.","rating":50.0,"popularity":1.0,"total_rating":50.0,"total_rating_count":0,"rating_count":0,"games":[34919,33603,36962,55888,65827,32283,25311,55308,25640,18623],"tags":[1,268435469,268435471,268435488],"category":0,"game_modes":[1,2,5],"themes":[1],"genres":[13,15,32],"first_release_date":1498176000000,"platforms":[6],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":6,"date":1498176000000,"